Brand story:
The innovative IBM begins its second century of existence
If someone were to look for a term that would define IBM's strategy very accurately, the closest would be "long term."
For the general public, IBM is the symbol of a technological revolution, a company that is perceived as current and yet a hundred years have passed since its foundation.
The basis of this long-term character was placed by the firm's first chief, the visionary Thomas J. Watson, sir.
Already he coined the motto that many problems in the world have a solution if people are willing to think.
