Location of impact.
Impact coordinates and the last radar aircraft record coincide, probably before the impact there was no loss of control or alteration in the flight path.
Dispersion of aircraft wreckage in a reduced area:
The information available so far suggests that the impact occurred on a straight and side trajectory.
The pattern of dispersion of the aircraft's wreckage suggests that the helicopter hit the ground under structural integrity conditions.
No evidence of fire or explosion has been detected:
Evidence remains undisclosed at the site of the disaster in the ship's remains of some kind of explosion or fire.
