Jiménez considered that microcredit is "a serious and rigorous policy dedicated to eradicating poverty," and now "more than ever" the governments of developed countries must work on solidarity criteria and not let it be a victim of the cuts.
For Spain, microcredit consists of "one of the main lines of development cooperation."
For her part, the Secretary of State for International Cooperation, Soraya Rodriguez, applauded "the success" of giving "confidence" to the people "excluded to whom everyone closes the doors"; and the mayor of Valladolid, Francisco Javier León de la Riva, welcomed those present to a city that "breaks its doors infected with the spirit of solidarity."
